Regulatory framework at the national and local level promotes:


(i) conservation of agrobiodiversity within current production systems and the adaptive capacity to cope with climate change;

(ii) implementation of in-situ and ex-situ conservation measures

target.comment:
National CC agencies generate climate and crop models that provide accurate and timely information to local stakeholders;




Extension services to increase farmer capacity regarding ABD conservation and management of climate resilient crop wild relatives;




Extension package in place in 4 pilot sites covering approx. 150,000 ha (each using one important landrace or locally adapted cultivar as entry point to ABD friendly, climate resilient production practices).

actual.comment:
To consolidate the success in facilitating implementation of ABD policies, legislation and regulation nationally and locally, in 2014-2015 the project made the inputs as below:

-	Catalogue of climate models up to 2030 has been prepared to be published in September 2015 and disseminated among stakeholders, local administration services, JRSs and farmers in order to ensure easy access to information and further replication of ABD practices;

-	Activities on practical use of the micro-loan approach were performed by the Jamoat Resource Center of one of the project areas to encourage farmers to organize and restore mother gardens of genetic resources;

-	Relevant interventions towards better conservation and adaptation of agrobiodiversity at local level were implemented in collaboration with the newly established Jamoat Resource Centre of Sarikhosor.

In general, over the years of implementation, a number of effective facilitation tools were developed and successfully applied through extension services offered to 10 model Jamoats, developed and disseminated documentation on the use of locally adapted cultivars, etc. Moreover, due to the project, extension services has become available on the basis of Jamoat Resource Centers (of which 2 are located in remote areas of Tajikistan), that makes them an effective facilitating mechanism at local level.  Totally 96 training and guiding materials, including 22 targeted training modules, were approbated during the project and made available at Jamoat Resource Centers.

